⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Natural Selection
node POP · POP · ⟦Natural Selection:POP:4138c6⟧

WHO   — Natural Selection — evolution as frequency change
WHAT  — The push on the gene pool: the alleles that reproduce more become more common, generation by generation.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because the heritable variants that leave more copies inherit the future.
HOW   — By raising the frequency of advantageous alleles and lowering the rest — measurable, predictable, real.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am not a story about giraffes; I am arithmetic on allele frequencies. Evolution is just me, counted.

